{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01G71riWFtmBfRji7b8YZT4b","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: view-contract-enforcer\n     3→description: Enforce request-validation, permission, service-handoff, and response-contract boundaries in views without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# View Contract Enforcer (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when adding or updating API views.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `view_name`\n    13→- `http_method`\n    14→- `request_schema_name`\n    15→- `response_schema_name`\n    16→- `service_symbol`\n    17→- `url_path`\n    18→- `url_name`\n    19→- `test_name`\n    20→- `test_url`\n    21→\n    22→## Execution Checklist\n    23→\n    24→1. Validate input at the view boundary before business logic.\n    25→2. Keep authorization checks explicit and close to entrypoint behavior.\n    26→3. Hand domain writes to a service function (`service_symbol`), not the view.\n    27→4. Return a stable response contract (`response_schema_name`).\n    28→5. Add route and test coverage for the new view path.\n    29→\n    30→## Guardrails\n    31→\n    32→- No domain write logic in view functions.\n    33→- No ad hoc payload parsing that bypasses the request contract.\n    34→- Include both success and access/validation behavior in tests.\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a484bec2-5575-4340-94db-b87178232a78","uuid":"11f169c5-8338-478b-8eee-9fb8e80f97c0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0112AsqrvpDKPezXemQYK8kM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file is a benign skill checklist document. Proceeding with the control skill checklist.\n\n# View Contract Enforcer Checklist\n\nApplying the skill to the specified view:\n\n**Variables**\n- view_name: `entity_summary`\n- http_method: `POST`\n- request_schema_name: `EntitySummaryRequest`\n- response_schema_name: `EntitySummaryResponse`\n- service_symbol: `build_entity_summary`\n- url_path: `entities/<int:pk>/summary/`\n- url_name: `entity-summary`\n- test_name: `test_entity_summary`\n- test_url: `/api/entities/1/summary/`\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n\n1. **Validate input at view boundary** — Deserialize/validate the POST body against `EntitySummaryRequest` before any business logic runs; return 400 on validation failure.\n2. **Explicit authorization at entrypoint** — Apply permission checks (e.g., `permission_classes` or explicit guard) tied to the entity `pk` before invoking the service.\n3. **Delegate domain work to service** — The view must call `build_entity_summary(pk, validated_data)` and must not perform writes, ORM mutations, or summary computation itself.\n4. **Stable response contract** — Serialize the service return value through `EntitySummaryResponse` and return it with a fixed status code; no ad hoc dict shapes.\n5. **Route + tests** — Register `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")` in the app's urls, and add `test_entity_summary` hitting `POST /api/entities/1/summary/` covering a success case plus at least one validation/access failure case.\n\n**Guardrails**\n- No domain writes inside `entity_summary`; all mutations live in `build_entity_summary`.\n- No manual `request.data` key-picking that bypasses `EntitySummaryRequest`.\n- Tests must assert both 2xx success and a 4xx validation/permission path."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":878,"cache_read_input_tokens":21535,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":878,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a484bec2-5575-4340-94db-b87178232a78","uuid":"af23d700-7280-480a-a054-bb7473139474"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":18837,"duration_api_ms":18651,"num_turns":8,"result":"The file is a benign skill checklist document. Proceeding with the control skill checklist.\n\n# View Contract Enforcer Checklist\n\nApplying the skill to the specified view:\n\n**Variables**\n- view_name: `entity_summary`\n- http_method: `POST`\n- request_schema_name: `EntitySummaryRequest`\n- response_schema_name: `EntitySummaryResponse`\n- service_symbol: `build_entity_summary`\n- url_path: `entities/<int:pk>/summary/`\n- url_name: `entity-summary`\n- test_name: `test_entity_summary`\n- test_url: `/api/entities/1/summary/`\n\n**Execution Checklist**\n\n1. **Validate input at view boundary** — Deserialize/validate the POST body against `EntitySummaryRequest` before any business logic runs; return 400 on validation failure.\n2. **Explicit authorization at entrypoint** — Apply permission checks (e.g., `permission_classes` or explicit guard) tied to the entity `pk` before invoking the service.\n3. **Delegate domain work to service** — The view must call `build_entity_summary(pk, validated_data)` and must not perform writes, ORM mutations, or summary computation itself.\n4. **Stable response contract** — Serialize the service return value through `EntitySummaryResponse` and return it with a fixed status code; no ad hoc dict shapes.\n5. **Route + tests** — Register `path(\"entities/<int:pk>/summary/\", entity_summary, name=\"entity-summary\")` in the app's urls, and add `test_entity_summary` hitting `POST /api/entities/1/summary/` covering a success case plus at least one validation/access failure case.\n\n**Guardrails**\n- No domain writes inside `entity_summary`; all mutations live in `build_entity_summary`.\n- No manual `request.data` key-picking that bypasses `EntitySummaryRequest`.\n- Tests must assert both 2xx success and a 4xx validation/permission path.","session_id":"a484bec2-5575-4340-94db-b87178232a78","total_cost_usd":0.33936825000000004